            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10492",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=martel",
                        "name": "martel",
                        "displayName": "Michal Minicki",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It also doesn't check if default is meeting this requirement. Not only in the assemble but also in the match method. \n\nI think it is programmers or webdesigners responsibility to create URLs correctly. If he submits incorrect value, he will quickly find out on a next URL check.  I don't think that runtime checking is neccessary here. And since assemble will be called multiple times in a single request, I would like to avoid the overhead.",
